CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper December 27, 1958, pg. 2, reads: "Homewood 'Slums' - The Health Department of Allegheny County, after numerous inspections, has found that these properties of Alfred E. Davis, located at 6828 to 6838 Frankstown Ave., contain violations of health regulations. Landlord Davis has been ordered to appear before Alderman Bruno on Dec. 29 to answer charges. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Row houses with second story balcony and arched windows, with billboard in background reading "...2nd Federal Savings and Loan Association..." 6828 - 6838 Frankstown Avenue, Homewood
